  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Cs have been measured on trapped ion quantum computers 95, 96, on an NMR quantum simulator 97 as well as on superconducting platforms 98, 99 including a measurement on a seven qutrit processor 100.",
    "In this section we discuss key results in DQS using variational quantum algorithms in a classical-quantum feedback loop.",
    "As such they operate with two main components: a quantum computer, which encodes the state of the system via a quantum circuit, and a classical computer, which optimizes the parameters of the quantum circuit to minimize a cost function.",
    "To evaluate the cost function measurements on the quantum state are performed and sent to the classical computer, which computes the cost function and optionally its derivative.",
    "In an iterative scheme the classical optimizer then proposes updated parameters of the circuit, which are sent to the quantum computer in order to find the optimal solution to the problem."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Cs have been measured on trapped ion quantum computers 95, 96, on an NMR quantum simulator 97 as well as on superconducting platforms 98, 99 including a measurement on a seven qutrit processor 100."
  ]
}